# Phase 1 — Data foundation
## Goal
Build a simple, clean dataset that the agent can query reliably. No agent code. No LLM calls. Minimum viable fields that answer the eval questions. Get it working fast and move to the agent.
## Business context
Simulating an Australian retail bank deposit book. Four customer segments, three lifecycle stages, real RBA rate history from Jan 2023 to Dec 2024. Simple enough to build in one session. Rich enough to answer meaningful business questions.
---
## Schema — three tables
### customer
| Field | Type | Values |
|-------------|------|--------|
| customer_id | TEXT | unique identifier |
| segment | TEXT | RETAIL_INDIVIDUAL, SELF_DIRECTED_INVESTOR, BUSINESS, INSTITUTIONAL |
| state | TEXT | NSW, VIC, QLD, WA, SA, ACT, TAS, NT |
| age_band | TEXT | 18-24, 25-34, 35-49, 50-64, 65+ — null for BUSINESS and INSTITUTIONAL |
| channel | TEXT | BRANCH, ONLINE, BROKER, PHONE |
| tenure_years | INT | 1-25 |
### deposit
| Field | Type | Values |
|-----------------|-------|--------|
| deposit_id | TEXT | unique identifier |
| customer_id | TEXT | foreign key to customer |
| term_months | INT | 1, 3, 6, 12, 24 |
| balance | FLOAT | AUD — log-normal by segment |
| advertised_rate | FLOAT | % p.a. |
| contracted_rate | FLOAT | % p.a. — always <= advertised_rate |
| nim | FLOAT | % p.a. — always positive |
| start_date | DATE | within Jan 2023 to Dec 2024 |
| maturity_date | DATE | start_date + term in months |
| status | TEXT | ACTIVE, MATURED, WITHDRAWN |
| lifecycle | TEXT | NEW_DEPOSIT, RENEWING, EXISTING |
### market_rates
| Field | Type | Values |
|----------------|-------|--------|
| week_start_date| DATE | one row per week |
| rba_cash_rate | FLOAT | actual RBA history |
