## Rate construction
advertised_rate = rba_cash_rate + segment_premium + term_premium
contracted_rate = advertised_rate - negotiation_discount
nim = contracted_rate - (rba_cash_rate - 0.30%)
### Segment premium
| Segment | Premium |
|------------------------|------------------|
| INSTITUTIONAL | -0.10% to 0.00% |
| BUSINESS | +0.00% to +0.20% |
| SELF_DIRECTED_INVESTOR | +0.10% to +0.30% |
| RETAIL_INDIVIDUAL | +0.20% to +0.50% |
### Term premium
| Term | Premium |
|-----------|---------|
| 1 month | +0.00% |
| 3 months | +0.10% |
| 6 months | +0.20% |
| 12 months | +0.35% |
| 24 months | +0.40% |
### Negotiation discount
| Segment | Discount |
|------------------------|-----------------|
| INSTITUTIONAL | 0.10% to 0.30% |
| SELF_DIRECTED_INVESTOR | 0.05% to 0.15% |
| BUSINESS | 0.00% to 0.10% |
| RETAIL_INDIVIDUAL | 0.00% to 0.05% |
### NIM targets
| Condition | NIM range |
|-----------------|----------------|
| Low rate period | 1.80% to 2.50% |
| High rate period | 1.20% to 1.80% |
NIM compresses as rates rise.
